    <div class="space-y-4">
      <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm"><summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer"><span class="font-heading font-medium text-gray-900">How long does installation take?</span><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-700 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg></summary><div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Most residential sprinkler systems take two to four days to install, depending on yard size and the number of zones. We trench, lay pipe, install heads, wire the controller, and test everything before we leave.</div></details>
      <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm"><summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer"><span class="font-heading font-medium text-gray-900">Can you add zones to my existing system?</span><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-700 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg></summary><div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Yes. If you've added landscaping or want better coverage in certain areas, we can tap into your existing system and add new zones without replacing what's already working.</div></details>
      <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm"><summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer"><span class="font-heading font-medium text-gray-900">Should I go with sprinklers or drip?</span><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-700 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg></summary><div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">It depends on what you're watering. Turf and ground covers do best with sprinklers. Individual plants, trees, shrubs, and xeriscape do best with drip. Most properties use a combination — sprinkler zones for lawn, drip zones for everything else.</div></details>
